FBIS4-40362 "drsov116_b_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-116 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues MVD, FCIS Reportedly Buying Foreign Arms MVD, FCIS Reportedly Buying Foreign Arms LD1506164694 Moscow NTV in Russian 1500 GMT 15 Jun 94 LD1506164694 Moscow NTV Russian BFN [Text] A POSFACTUM correspondent has been told by competent sources that the Russian Internal Affairs Ministry [MVD] and the counterintelligence service are buying foreign weapons and ammunition at the instruction of Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin. On the list are pistols, automatic weapons, and revolvers manufactured by famous Western firms. Tens of thousands of units of ammunition have been bought for each type of weapon. It seems that the authorities are set to undertake an uncompromising fight against bandits. But what form it is to take now can only be guessed at.
